metadata.name: İşullana
metadata.description: Ishtar is the name of the Akkadian goddess of love and fertility, and the daughter of the air goddess Anu. Inana, Innina in the Sumerian pantheon; Annimutu in Babylon; It was called Ashtar in Phoenician, and it was accepted as Astarte in Greek religion. Ishullana is Anu's gardener and is in love with Anu's daughter, Ishtar.
